    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This may be a more subtle inconsistency: we automatically convert units for literals in-line without raising an error.\r\n\r\nIn most cases this is okay, as `my_var: uint256(\"my_unit\"); self.my_var = 1  # my_units` is more readable than `my_var: uint256(\"my_unit\"); self.my_var = convert(1, \"my_unit\")`. But in your case, it's a bit of a quandary because it sort of hides the fact that your `min_tokens(wei)` is 1 (should `wei` be a custom unit? e.g. `token`) which is a bit harder to appreciate when reading the code.\r\n\r\nWe may need to more fully think through the whole units thing :/",
